Diagram 1 (Typical Bad Move)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par It is a typical bad move for white to play dansu at 1. As soon as black connects at 2, black's group is perfectly alive.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Black \'a1\'e3 is positioned perfectly. After black 4 is played, it hurts that white cannot connect at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 .
\par }
