Diagram 3 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par The placement of white 1 leaves black helpless.
\par
\par If black resists at 2, White 3 finishes black off.
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Because of a shortage of liberties, black can't play at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 .
\par \pard
\par Instead of 2, if black plays at 3, white plays at 2 and black is still dead.
\par }
