Diagram 4 (A Difficult Problem)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In the beginning, if white 1 and black 2 were not played, it would have been quite a difficult problem.
\par You should be at least 5k if you can solve this problem.
\par
\par Black 1 is played according to the proverb stating, "there is death in a hane" so it is not too difficult, but because you have to read up to 3, it is  a little tricky.
\par }
